Since this cohort is the full reporting period, it is possible for the sum of the project-level counts to be greater than the CoC-wide count if people were served in multiple projects during the period. That largest possible value is equal to the CoC-wide value multiplied by the number of projects (of this project type) serving any of these people. (For instance, if the CoC-wide count for this project type was 20, and if there were 4 projects of this type that served at least one of these people, then the largest possible value for the sum of the project-level counts would be 20*4=80 since those 20 people could have been served in each of the 4 projects.)
